Professor Charles Chukwuma Soludo, Anambra State governor-elect has appointed former Vice President of the World Bank, Dr. Oby Ezekwesili, chairperson of his transition committee, according to an exclusive story published late Thursday morning, January 13, 2022, by TheNiche. Soludo won the Anambra Governorship election held on November 6, 2021 convincingly, winning outright in 19 out of the 21 local governments in the state. He won on the platform of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA). TheNiche said it was informed by reliable sources that the inauguration of the committee will take place on Thursday, January 20, at the Agulu Lake (Golden Tulip) Hotel, Awka. Senator Andy Uba has boasted that he made his opponent in the upcoming Anambra governorship election, Charles Soludo the Central Bank of Nigeria governor. Professor Charles Soludo is the candidate of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) Governor while Uba is the candidate of the All Progressives Congress. During a… In "News" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - Mrs. Oby Ezekwesili, former World Bank Vice President and former minister of  education in Nigeria, is to deliver the Fifth Anniversary Lecture of Realnews Magazine scheduled to hold on Thursday, November 16. Ezekwesili, who is the co-founder of Transparency International, will speak on 'African Leadership in… In "News" Obiano To Unveil New Book On Anambra Light Bearers In "News"